alert.note: Alert for Coastal Dixie; Coastal Taylor (Florida) Issued by the National Weather Service

info.headline: Coastal Flood Advisory issued January 10 at 3:37AM EST until January 10 at 7:00AM EST by NWS Tallahassee
info.description: ...COASTAL FLOOD ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 7 AM EST THIS MORNING... * WHAT...Minor coastal flooding. * WHERE...Coastal Taylor and Coastal Dixie Counties. * WHEN...Until 7 AM EST Wednesday. * IMPACTS...With high tide at 1130 pm ET Tuesday night, water levels will once again rise with persistent onshore flow and result in minor coastal flooding for areas in Taylor and Dixie County. Water may briefly overtop seawalls resulting in inundation of 1 to 3 feet above normally dry ground. This will result in flooding of roads and water covering the ground near residential structures.
info.instruction: If travel is required, allow extra time as some roads may be closed. Do not drive around barricades or through water of unknown depth. Take the necessary actions to protect flood-prone property.
